OL,4,Cleft with nothing - is your plan safe?
OL,6,FAn ongoing fraud investigation into
OL,7,Fthe collapsed firm is underway, with
OL,8,Fmillions of pounds believed to be in
OL,9,Fthe Cayman Islands.
OL,11,FSince July 2022, funeral plans have
OL,12,Fbeen regulated by the Financial
OL,13,FConduct Authority, including
OL,14,Fcompensation if firms go bust.
OL,16,FSafe Hands Plans Ltd, with 70,000
OL,17,Fcustomers, collapsed in 2022. One Life
OL,18,FFuneral Planning Ltd, with 13,700 plan
OL,19,Fholders, went bust after officials
OL,20,Frefused to authorise the company under
OL,21,Fthe new rules two years ago.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
